THE RATWAY & THE WARRENS: ESBERN'S RESCUE
Standalone Dungeon Module — Riften Underground Party Tier: Expert (AP 10) | Estimated Runtime: 2-3 hours

DUNGEON DASHBOARD
Function: The party descends into Riften's sewers to rescue a paranoid fugitive from a Thalmor kill squad. Along the way they navigate Thieves Guild territory, discover the forgotten people beneath the city, find evidence of Thalmor operations that reframe the entire geopolitical landscape, and recover Blades intelligence that teases Sky Haven Temple.
The Clock: The Thalmor hit squad entered the Ratway approximately 30 minutes before the party. They are methodically searching door to door. Esbern's reinforced door will hold for roughly 1 hour of in-game time. The party does not need to rush blindly — but lingering in the Ragged Flagon for an hour of shopping will get Esbern killed.
Pacing Tool: After every scene the party spends significant time in, roll a d6. On a 1-2, the party hears a distant BOOM echo through the tunnels — the mercs breaching another door. This is atmospheric pressure, not a mechanical timer. Use it to keep them moving.
Light: The Ratway has intermittent torchlight — enough to see by in the main corridors, pitch dark in side passages. The Warrens have almost no light. Characters without darkvision or a light source fight with Disadvantage in the Warrens.
Danger Level (Short Rest): TN 7 (Exposed) throughout. TN 3 (Suicidal) once the Thalmor are alerted to the party's presence.

MAP OVERVIEW
The dungeon has three layers, each deeper and darker than the last:
LAYER 1: THE RATWAY (Sewers)
├── Scene 1: The Descent (Entry + Guild Sentries)
└── Scene 2: The Ragged Flagon (Thieves Guild Hub)

LAYER 2: THE WARRENS (Sub-Sewers)
└── Scene 3: The Forgotten (Destitute + Dead Blade + Thalmor Intel)

LAYER 3: THE VAULTS (Deepest Level)
├── Scene 4: The Ratway Race (Thalmor Combat)
└── Scene 5: Esbern's Bunker (Reward + Lore Dump)


