SCENE 1: THE DESCENT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Function: Party enters the Ratway and encounters the Thieves Guild's outer security, establishing the tone and getting directions deeper.
Location: The sewer entrance beneath Riften's lower marketplace. Accessible through a grate near the canal or a wooden door in the foundation of the marketplace platform.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"The staircase drops you below the canal level into a low-ceilinged tunnel of ancient stonework slick with condensation and canal runoff. The air is thick — wet stone, rotting food, and something acrid underneath that catches in your throat. Torches are jammed into iron brackets at irregular intervals, casting uneven orange light that makes the shadows move.
Ahead, the tunnel splits. The left fork is wider and better-lit — you can hear distant voices, the clink of glass, a woman laughing. The right fork is narrow and dark, descending steeply. A crude sign is nailed to the wall at the junction: a painted tankard pointing left, and a painted skull pointing right.
Sitting on an overturned barrel at the junction is a wiry Breton man with a crossbow across his knees. He watches you come down the stairs with the flat, patient expression of someone who has watched a lot of people come down those stairs."
Then improvise from: The drip of water echoing. Rats skittering at the edges of torchlight. The distant sound of the Flagon is warm and inviting — fiddle music, raised voices. The right fork smells worse and the air is colder.
WHAT'S IN THIS ROOM
The junction sign (tankard left, skull right): What they see: A crude wooden sign with painted symbols. If they investigate: The tankard points to the Ragged Flagon (Scene 2). The skull points deeper — the Warrens (Scene 3) and the Vaults beyond. The paint on the skull is fresher. Someone re-painted it recently. Why planted here: Navigation. Players need to understand the layout immediately.
The sentry on the barrel (Dirge): What they see: A wiry Breton man with a crossbow, watching them. If they investigate: He's the Guild's outer security. He decides who passes. See NPC block below. Why planted here: The Guild controls this chokepoint. He's the first social gate.
The sounds from the left fork: What they see: Warm light, voices, music. If they investigate: The Ragged Flagon. Going there is safe but costs time (see Dungeon Clock). Why planted here: Establishes the Flagon as an option and creates the time-pressure choice.
The cold air from the right fork: What they see: Darkness, descending tunnel, worse smell. If they investigate: Direct route to the Warrens. Faster to Esbern but skips the Guild's information. Why planted here: Gives the party a bypass option if they want to rush.
THE PEOPLE
DIRGE (Guild Sentry) Voice: Flat, bored, Breton accent. Speaks in short sentences. Doesn't waste words on people he doesn't respect. Body language: Doesn't stand when they approach. Stays seated. Crossbow stays across his knees. Attitude: Neutral-to-hostile. He doesn't know them. He doesn't care about them. Cooperates for: Gold (50+), name-dropping Brynjolf, or mentioning Maven. Pisses him off: Threats, showing weapons, mentioning the Dark Brotherhood, acting like they own the place.
Opening line: "That's far enough. The Flagon's left. You want a drink, you pay the house tax — ten gold a head. You want the Warrens..." He looks at the skull sign. "Nobody wants the Warrens."
If asked about:
Topic
Response
The old man (Esbern)
"There's a hermit down in the Vaults. Been there longer than I've had this post. Pays his rent. Doesn't bother anyone. Why?"
Strangers / visitors today
His eyes narrow. "Four of them. Elves. Well-armed. Came through maybe half an hour ago. Paid double and told me to forget their faces." A beat. "I took the gold. I didn't forget."
The Warrens
"Skooma den. Sick people. Argonians who can't afford the docks. You go down there, don't touch anything, don't drink anything, and don't make promises to anyone."
The Thieves Guild
"I don't know what you're talking about." Said with zero conviction.
The Thalmor
"I said four elves. You want to call them something, that's your business. They went right. Down toward the Vaults."

THE MOVES
ANY PC → GETTING PAST DIRGE
What they want: Access to the Ratway. What's required: Payment, persuasion, or force.
Pay the tax (10 gold/head) └─→ Dirge pockets the coin, jerks his thumb left. "Flagon's through there. Behave." └─→ If they ask to go RIGHT: "Skull side's free. I'm not charging people to walk into misery."
Intimidate (Might or Guile, Hard -2) ├─ SUCCESS → Dirge stands slowly. "Fine. Go wherever you want. But Brynjolf hears about this." └─ FAILURE → Dirge levels the crossbow. "Try that again." Does not fire unless attacked. Reinforcements from the Flagon arrive in 2 rounds if fighting starts.
Mention the elves went toward the old man └─→ Dirge's expression changes. Not concern — calculation. "If those four are heading for the hermit, that's his problem. Unless you're offering to make it mine." └─→ He'll sell Esbern's exact location for 100 gold: "Bottom of the Vaults. Reinforced door, three locks. Can't miss it — it's the only door down there that isn't rotting."
ORION → GUILD INTELLIGENCE (if he identifies himself carefully)
What he wants: Information about Grelod's pipeline. What's required: Proving he's Brotherhood or Guild-adjacent.
Show the Black Sacrament token (Guile, Standard) ├─ SUCCESS → Dirge goes very still. Nods once. "You want the Flagon. Ask for Delvin. Tell him the Night Mother sent a friend." └─ FAILURE → Dirge doesn't recognize the token or doesn't trust Orion's presentation. "I don't know what that is." Shuts down.
EXIT
Party can proceed LEFT to the Ragged Flagon (Scene 2) or RIGHT/DOWN to the Warrens (Scene 3). Key info available: The Thalmor are 30 minutes ahead. They went toward the Vaults. Esbern's location is buyable. Likely next: Scene 2 (Flagon) if they want information, Scene 3 (Warrens) if they want speed.

