Function: Party passes through the Warrens — Riften's lowest level of humanity — and discovers a dead Blades agent carrying Sky Haven Temple intelligence AND a Thalmor dispatch case containing operational orders that reveal the scope of the Dominion's true agenda. The Thalmor mercs came through here and left damage.
Location: Below the Ragged Flagon. The Warrens are not a tavern or a guild hall — they are a shantytown built into abandoned sewer infrastructure. Makeshift shelters of salvaged wood and canvas line the tunnels. The air is thick with skooma smoke, unwashed bodies, and despair.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"The tunnel descends sharply and the light dies. What torches exist here are guttering tallow candles wedged into cracks in the stone. The ceiling is lower. The walls are wet.
People live here. You see them in the dim light — shapes huddled against the walls under layers of rags. An Argonian woman sits against a pillar, staring at nothing, her scales dull and flaking. Two Nord men share a skooma pipe in a doorway, their eyes glassy. A child — human, maybe eight — darts between shelters carrying a clay jug of water.
The tunnel ahead shows fresh damage. A wooden door has been kicked off its hinges. A shelf of meagre possessions has been swept to the floor. Someone came through here fast and violent and did not care what they broke.
Against the far wall, slumped in an alcove between two shelters, is a body. Not a Warren resident — the clothes are too good. Travel-worn leathers, a courier's satchel, and a short sword still in its scabbard. The body is fresh. Hours old. The throat has been cut with surgical precision."
Then improvise from: The smell is overpowering — skooma sweet-smoke, urine, rot. The quiet. People down here don't talk much. The child with the water jug stops to stare at the party with enormous eyes, then runs.

