WHAT'S IN THIS ROOM
The kicked-in door and scattered belongings: What they see: Fresh damage. Someone forced their way through. If they investigate: Thalmor mercs. They searched this shelter and moved on. The resident — an old Argonian man — is sitting in the wreckage of his home, bleeding from a cut on his head where they struck him. He'll talk (see Stands-In-Shadows below). Why planted here: Establishes Thalmor brutality in the party's direct experience.
The dead body in the alcove (Caius Varro, Blades agent): What they see: A fresh corpse with a courier's satchel. Not a Warren resident. If they investigate: This is a Blades agent who was trying to reach Esbern. The Thalmor found him first. His satchel contains critical lore. See detailed breakdown below. Why planted here: The Blades lore teaser and the emotional stakes of what happens when the Thalmor catch someone.
The Argonian woman staring at nothing: What they see: A sick Argonian. If they investigate: Skooma addiction, late stage. She won't respond to conversation. She represents what happens to people down here — she's atmosphere, not a quest.
