The Thalmor took Caius's journal but missed a folded sheaf of papers that had slipped under the courier's body during the struggle. It is a Thalmor dispatch case — oiled leather, sealed with the Aldmeri eagle. The seal is broken (Caius intercepted it).
Inside: three documents in Aldmeris with a partial Common translation in Caius's handwriting. This is what the Thalmor are actually doing. Read the following to the players slowly. Let it land.
Document 1: Operational Order — "Directive: Controlled Neglect"
Caius's translation notes: "Orders from Elenwen to all field commanders. Re: the Dagon cult activity at the Eldergleam and the Throat of the World."
"Do not engage Dagonist operatives unless they directly threaten Dominion assets. The corruption of Skyrim's root network and the destabilization of Snow-Throat serve our strategic objectives. A weakened Tower is easier to unbind than a healthy one. Let the cultists do the foundational work. We will harvest the result."
Document 2: Strategic Assessment — "The Tower Protocol: Phase 2"
Caius's translation notes: "This is the real plan. Gods help us."
"With the deactivation of White-Gold and Red Mountain, only two primary Towers remain active in the northern theater: Snow-Throat (Throat of the World) and Crystal-Like-Law (destroyed, but its echo persists in the Summerset archives). The unbinding of Snow-Throat will eliminate the final metaphysical anchor stabilizing the mortal plane in Skyrim."
"To be clear for field personnel: the objective is not conquest. Conquest preserves the structure of the world. The objective is dissolution. The mortal plane is a prison constructed by the trickster god Lorkhan to trap the divine spirits of the Mer in flesh. Every Tower is a bar in that cage. Every Tower we unbind brings us closer to liberation — the restoration of the Mer to their original, divine state of pure spirit."
"The cost to the mortal races is total. The dissolution of the mortal plane ends physical existence for all beings bound to it. This is not a side effect. This is the intended outcome. The races of Man were created BY the prison. When the prison falls, they cease to exist. We do not mourn architecture."
Document 3: Field Intelligence — "Asset Report: Skyrim"
Caius's translation notes: "They're tracking everyone. Including the Wardens."
A list of tracked individuals and assets. Most names are in Aldmeris, but Caius has translated several:
"Obsidian Lanterns — Priority observation. Dragon-killers. Politically unstable. The Imperial woman (Caelus) is leverage against her father. The vampire is a biological weapon. The Khajiit is neutralized (confirm). The elf-priestess is a Kynareth conduit — monitor for Tower Protocol implications. Recommend: continued surveillance. Do not engage until Heat Level warrants."
"Krusp Fanck — Independent Dragon Cult hunter. Effective but uncontrollable. Recommend: terminate if he interferes with Directive operations."
"Esbern — Last known Blade. Location: Riften Ratway. Extraction team deployed. He has been searching for Alduin's Wall. He cannot be allowed to find it. The Wall contains information about Dragonrend. If the Lanterns acquire Dragonrend, our Dragon capture program becomes untenable."
THE MOVES
ANY PC → INVESTIGATING CAIUS'S BODY
What they want: Information. What's required: Looking at the body and the satchel.
Examine the body (no roll needed) └─→ Throat cut. Single stroke. Professional. He didn't suffer long but he saw it coming — his hand is still reaching for the satchel.
Search the satchel (no roll needed) └─→ Find the letter to Esbern and the dropped Thalmor dispatch case. Both are critical quest items.
Read the Thalmor documents (Magic TN 14 to translate the untranslated Aldmeris portions) ├─ SUCCESS → Full translation of all three documents. The party now knows the Tower Protocol. ├─ FAILURE → They get Caius's partial translations (the Common text above). Still devastating, just incomplete. └─→ Esbern can translate the rest in Scene 5 if they bring them to him.
SAIJAH or DANICA → MILA'S MOTHER
What they want: To help a sick woman. What's required: Any healing magic or a potion.
Heal the mother (any Restoration spell or potion) └─→ The woman — Nord, mid-thirties, emaciated — gasps and sits up. She's been sick for weeks. Canal fever, not plague. Treatable. She clutches Mila and weeps. Mila stares at the healer like they hung the moons. └─→ No mechanical reward. The reward is Mila's face.
TRIGGERED EVENT: THE THIRD BOOM
Setup: The pacing d6 has been rolling. By now, the party should have heard 1-2 distant impacts.
Trigger: Entering the tunnel that descends from the Warrens to the Vaults.
"As you enter the downward tunnel, a BOOM shakes dust from the ceiling. Closer this time. Much closer. You hear a muffled voice — clipped, authoritative, speaking Aldmeris — and then the splintering crash of another door being forced. The echoes bounce off the stone, making it impossible to tell exactly how far ahead they are. But they are ahead. And they are getting closer to the bottom."
What the party now knows:
The Thalmor are in the Vaults
They are breaching doors systematically
Esbern's door is next or near-next
If they pursue: → Scene 4 (The Ratway Race) If they don't: The Thalmor breach Esbern's door. He dies. The Dragonstone quest dies with him.
EXIT
Party has Blades intelligence (Sky Haven Temple, Alduin's Wall, Dragonrend) and Thalmor intelligence (Tower Protocol, Controlled Neglect, the asset tracking list). They know the Thalmor are close to Esbern. Key items: Caius's letter, Thalmor dispatch case. Orion: Grelod intelligence (from Scene 2) ✓ Hook planted: Sky Haven Temple for a future arc. Likely next: Scene 4 (The Ratway Race) — urgently.

