Ahead, maybe sixty feet, you see it: a cold blue-white glow moving in the dark. Magelight. And in that light, four figures. Three are armored — you catch the glint of golden-hued metal beneath dark cloaks. They stand in a wedge formation facing a heavy iron-banded door. The fourth stands behind them, staff raised, the magelight hovering above their head.
The leader — tall, lean, wearing a hooded cloak over gilded armor — presses a gauntleted hand against the door and speaks a word of power. The door shudders. Frost crackles across its surface. He's trying to freeze the lock mechanism to shatter it.
He hasn't seen you yet. The darkness behind them is absolute. You have seconds."
