What she wants: To understand the strategic landscape. What's required: Showing Esbern the Thalmor documents and/or asking about the dragon threat.
Show documents + ask about priorities └─→ Esbern lays it out: "You have three enemies. The Dragon Cult wants to resurrect Alduin and enslave the world under dragon rule. The Dagon cult wants to corrupt the Eldergleam and unmake the natural order. The Thalmor want to dissolve reality itself." "The Dragon Cult is the immediate threat — dragons are rising NOW. The Dagon cult is the escalating threat — their corruption is spreading. The Thalmor are the existential threat — their plan, if completed, ends everything." "You need the Dragonstone to fight the dragons. You need to reach Sky Haven Temple to learn Dragonrend. And you need to do both before the Thalmor find the Wall first and destroy it."
ESBERN → JOINING THE PARTY (Conditional)
Esbern will not stay in the Ratway. The Thalmor found him. His bunker is compromised. He needs to move.
If the party offers to take him: └─→ "I am old. I am not a fighter. But I have spent thirty years preparing for this moment and I will not waste it dying in a sewer. Take me somewhere safe — an inn, a safehouse, anywhere the Thalmor won't look — and I will be your Dragon Cult expert. Every piece of intelligence I have is yours."
Where to put him: Esbern can stay at the Bee and Barb (risky — public), be sent to a Warden safehouse (if one exists), or travel with the party (he is a liability in combat but invaluable for lore). This is the party's decision.
